annotationA: Copper transporter 1B ensures copper uptake in the intestine. The transcription of the gene is upregulated under conditions of copper depletion via the metal-responsive transcription factor MTF-1
annotationB: ATP7, isoform B; Copper-exporting ATPase activity; copper ion transmembrane transporter activity; nucleotide binding; copper ion binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: copper ion transport; larval development; developmental pigmentation; adult chitin-containing cuticle pigmentation; metal ion homeostasis; cellular copper ion homeostasis
